                <h1 class="mb-4">Eidos User Guide</h1>
                <p class="lead">Welcome to Eidos! This guide will help you get started building ontologies, collaborating with others, and making the most of the platform.</p>

                <!-- Getting Started -->
                <section id="getting-started" class="doc-section">
                    <h2><i class="bi bi-rocket text-primary"></i> Getting Started</h2>

                    <h3>What is an Ontology?</h3>
                    <p>An ontology is a structured way to organize knowledge about a domain. It consists of:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Concepts</strong> - The things in your domain (e.g., "Dog", "Animal", "Pet")</li>
                        <li><strong>Relationships</strong> - How concepts relate to each other (e.g., "Dog is-a Animal")</li>
                        <li><strong>Properties</strong> - Attributes that describe concepts</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> <strong>Example:</strong> If you're building an ontology for a pet store, you might have concepts like "Dog", "Cat", "Food", and "Toy", with relationships like "Dog needs-a Food" or "Cat is-a Pet".
                    </div>

                    <h3>Your First Login</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Sign in using your preferred method (Google, GitHub, Microsoft, or Entra ID)</li>
                        <li>You'll see your dashboard with any existing workspaces</li>
                        <li>Click "Create New Workspace" to get started</li>
                    </ol>

                    <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
                        <i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> <strong>Workspaces vs Ontologies:</strong> Eidos is workspace-first! When you create a workspace, an ontology is automatically created for it. Workspaces combine structured knowledge (ontologies) with flexible note-taking in one integrated environment.
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- Creating a Workspace -->
                <section id="creating-ontology" class="doc-section">
                    <h2><i class="bi bi-plus-circle text-primary"></i> Creating a Workspace</h2>

                    <h3>Quick Start</h3>
                    <ol>
                        <li>From your dashboard, click the <span class="badge bg-success">Create New Workspace</span> button</li>
                        <li>Enter a descriptive name for your workspace (e.g., "E-commerce Product Catalog")</li>
                        <li>Optionally add a description to explain its purpose</li>
                        <li>Choose your privacy settings (see below)</li>
                        <li>Click <strong>Create Workspace</strong></li>
                    </ol>

                    <div class="alert alert-success">
                        <i class="bi bi-check-circle"></i> <strong>What happens next:</strong> Eidos automatically creates an ontology for your workspace (version 0.1), sets up note-taking capabilities, configures your chosen permissions, and opens the workspace view where you can start adding concepts and notes!
                    </div>

                    <h3>Privacy & Access Control</h3>
                    <p>When creating a workspace, you can configure who has access right from the start:</p>

                    <h4>Privacy Levels</h4>
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                            <div class="card h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">üîí Private</h5>
                                    <p class="card-text">Only you can access this workspace. You can invite specific users later.</p>
                                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0"><strong>Best for:</strong> Personal projects, early drafts</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                            <div class="card h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">üë• Group</h5>
                                    <p class="card-text">Shared with members of a specific user group. Perfect for team collaboration!</p>
                                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0"><strong>Best for:</strong> Team projects, departments, research groups</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-md-4 mb-3">
                            <div class="card h-100">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <h5 class="card-title">üåç Public</h5>
                                    <p class="card-text">Anyone with the link can view this workspace. Appears in public listings.</p>
                                    <p class="text-muted small mb-0"><strong>Best for:</strong> Open knowledge bases, public documentation</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h4>Group-Based Sharing</h4>
                    <p>When you select "Group" privacy, you can create a new group or use an existing one:</p>

                    <div class="card mb-3">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h6>Create a New Group (Inline)</h6>
                            <ol>
                                <li>Select <strong>Group</strong> privacy level</li>
                                <li>In the "Select Group" dropdown, choose <strong>+ Create New Group</strong></li>
                                <li>Enter a group name (e.g., "Research Team Alpha")</li>
                                <li>Add group members using the user picker (type to search by name or email)</li>
                                <li>Create your workspace - the group and permissions are set up automatically!</li>
                            </ol>
                            <div class="alert alert-info small mb-0">
                                <i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i> Groups you create are reusable! You can use the same group for multiple workspaces.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card mb-3">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h6>Use an Existing Group</h6>
                            <ol>
                                <li>Select <strong>Group</strong> privacy level</li>
                                <li>In the "Select Group" dropdown, choose from your existing groups</li>
                                <li>All group members automatically get <strong>View, Add & Edit</strong> permissions</li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h4>Direct User Access</h4>
                    <p>You can also grant access to specific users individually, regardless of privacy level:</p>

                    <div class="card mb-3">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h6>How to Grant Direct Access</h6>
                            <ol>
                                <li>Check the box "Grant access to specific users"</li>
                                <li>Use the user picker to search and select users</li>
                                <li>Choose their permission level:
                                    <ul>
                                        <li><span class="badge bg-info">View</span> - Read-only access</li>
                                        <li><span class="badge bg-success">View & Add</span> - Can add new content</li>
                                        <li><span class="badge bg-warning text-dark">View, Add & Edit</span> - Can modify existing content (default)</li>
                                        <li><span class="badge bg-danger">Full Access</span> - Administrative permissions</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </li>
                                <li>Users get immediate access when the workspace is created</li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <h4>User Picker</h4>
                    <p>The user picker makes it easy to find and select collaborators:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Smart Search:</strong> Type at least 2 characters to search by name or email</li>
                        <li><strong>Prioritized Results:</strong> Users you've collaborated with before appear first with a "Past collaborator" badge</li>
                        <li><strong>Multi-Select:</strong> Click users to add them, click the X on badges to remove</li>
                        <li><strong>Visual Feedback:</strong> See user initials and names at a glance</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="alert alert-info">
                        <i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Tip:</strong> Use clear, descriptive names that reflect the domain or project. Examples: "Healthcare Terminology", "Product Taxonomy", "Research Notes - AI Ethics"
                    </div>

                    <h3>Public Workspace Options</h3>
                    <p>When creating a public workspace, you have an additional option:</p>
                    <div class="form-check mb-3">
                        <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" disabled>
                        <label class="form-check-label">
                            <strong>Allow anyone to edit</strong> (not just view)
                        </label>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-muted">When enabled, anyone with the link can add and edit content in your workspace - perfect for wikis and community knowledge bases!</p>

                    <h3>After Creation</h3>
                    <p>Once your workspace is created, you can:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>View Permissions:</strong> Go to Settings > Permissions to see who has access</li>
                        <li><strong>Manage Groups:</strong> View group members and their permission levels</li>
                        <li><strong>Add More Users:</strong> Grant additional users access anytime</li>
                        <li><strong>Change Privacy:</strong> Update visibility and permissions in Settings</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>Navigating Your Workspace</h3>
                    <p>Once created, you can switch between different views:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Workspace View</strong> - Three-pane note-taking interface with concept links</li>
                        <li><strong>Ontology Graph View</strong> - Visual graph of concepts and relationships (click "Switch to Ontology" button)</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="alert alert-warning">
                        <i class="bi bi-exclamation-triangle"></i> <strong>Legacy Note:</strong> If you have older ontologies created before the workspace feature, don't worry! They automatically get workspaces when you access them. All your existing work is preserved.
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- Working with Concepts -->
                <section id="concepts" class="doc-section">
                    <h2><i class="bi bi-box text-primary"></i> Working with Concepts</h2>

                    <h3>Adding Concepts</h3>
                    <p>There are several ways to add concepts:</p>

                    <h4>Method 1: Add Concept Button</h4>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Click <span class="badge bg-success"><i class="bi bi-plus-circle"></i> Add Concept</span></li>
